items.content:
Hello everybody,

Today's class is going to be slightly different from the other classes that I have taught you. Today we are going to work on "Wikiwijs", individually.

You are going to learn about a new subject and a new theme. In the next slide we are going to get more into that.

Important things to note:

  1. '<' and '>' are used to skip through assignments.
  2. For some a assignments you will need headphones or earbuds.
  3. If you have any questions please notify me via teams

Good luck and enjoy your assignments!

Today we are going to focus on introducing yourself.

At the end of this class you will know:

  • What qualities are.
  • How to make scentences using the new qualities you learned.
  • How to introduce yourself using your qualities.

Today we are going to focus on introducing yourself.

  • What is important to note when you introduce yourself?
  • What is the first things you think of when you introduce yourself?

items.title: Make a mind map
items.description: Use this link to answer the previous questions about introducing yourself. Make sure to make a print screen of your mind map once you are done. Try to come up with at least 5 things to write down.

items.content: You just saw a couple of qualities in the video. In the next assignment you are going to learn a couple of good qualities that you might have.

content.body:
If you are brave in your thinking and daring in your actions, you can accomplish anything.

Goals provide governance to vision and mission, guiding people and organizations to a meaningful purpose.

Leadership with humility means service to others, ownership of your own mistakes and failures, and openness to learning.

Leading with intuition and intelligence gives everyone around you room to grow.

Good leaders speak; great leaders listen. When you're listening to others, you're learning from them.

Mentor and encourage those around you. Inspire them to take chances.

Show people they can count on you in good times and bad by living up to your word. Be dependable and consistent.

When you're encouraging, caring and sympathetic and helpful, offering feedback both positive and negative, you give those around you the confidence they need to persist.

You have faith in those you're leading, and they will have faith in you.

Wise

Wisdom in leadership is more than just being wise--it's using that wisdom to give insight and inspiration to others.

items.content: Now we are going to look at the negative qualities!

content.body:
Used to describe a young person who is confident in a way that is unpleasant and sometimes rude

Childlike, acts like a child

Does not like being around people or talk to people

doing something a lot and unable to stop doing it, like smoking/ drinking.

To order, limit, or rule something, or someone's actions or behavior

Does not tell the truth, is a liar.

Isn't calm. Worried.

A person who wants everything to be perfect

Wanting a lot more money, clothes etc. than you need

Shy.

items.content: Watch this video of me introducing myself and try to write down as many qualities about me as you can. These can of course be negative and positive. Lets see how many you can catch.

items.caption: Me, Myself and I: introduce myself

items.content:
Now it is your turn! Write a script for your introduction of yourself. Make sure to do the following.

What?

  1. Say your name.
  2. Tell us your age.
  3. Tell us where you are from or talk about your hobbies.
  4. 2 good qualities, give 2 examples.
  5. 2 bad qualities, give 2 examples.

Bonus:

  • Tell us how you are going to improve yourself.

How long?

15 minutes

With whom?

alone

Need help?

watch the video, or call via teams

Need a challenge?

do the bonus assignment!

Done?

Upload your script on teams, assignment: "Wikiwijs"

Do you still struggle a bit with different kind of qualities and what they mean? Then the next assignment is for you. The assignment is called "extra practice". If you think, I got this Ms. Madmar. Then you may skip to the next assignment, "extra exercise".

items.title: Feedback
items.description: Vul het formulier in en stuur je feedback op. Na het invullen ben je klaar met je Wikiwijs. Ik wil je heel graag bedanken voor het maken van mijn Wikiwijs en hoop dat je er wat van hebt opgestoken.
